23
00:02:36,440 --> 00:02:37,000
Say it.

24
00:02:37,680 --> 00:02:38,680
Say I'm not afraid of the cold.

25
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:46,560
Why are you so useless?

26
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:50,160
Pick it up.

27
00:02:51,079 --> 00:02:51,600
Hurry.

28
00:02:53,760 --> 00:02:54,400
Hurry up.

29
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:57,160
Be good, pick it up.

30
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:00,440
That ice cube.

31
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:04,760
Can't even do this one little thing.

32
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:08,840
Hold it,

33
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:09,600
you hear me?

34
00:03:11,920 --> 00:03:13,280
No whining.

35
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:14,000
One,

36
00:03:15,760 --> 00:03:16,120
two.

37
00:03:16,360 --> 00:03:17,280
In your head,

38
00:03:17,440 --> 00:03:18,360
say "I'm not afraid of the cold."

39
00:03:18,760 --> 00:03:20,160
Say it: I'm not afraid of the cold.

40
00:03:22,079 --> 00:03:23,120
Say it.

41
00:03:34,160 --> 00:03:34,840
[Ailing,]

42
00:03:35,920 --> 00:03:36,720
[it's me.]

43
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:46,680
[Ailing, are you home?]

44
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:48,160
[It's Feng.]

45
00:03:55,880 --> 00:03:56,480
[Ailing,]

46
00:03:59,120 --> 00:03:59,880
[it's Feng.]

47
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:04,160
Coming, coming.

48
00:04:15,360 --> 00:04:15,920
Feng.

49
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:18,640
Are you feeling okay?

50
00:04:19,720 --> 00:04:20,399
I'm fine.

51
00:04:20,880 --> 00:04:21,760
Really, I'm fine.

52
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:23,200
Good.

53
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:25,600
Do you want to come in?

54
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:26,240
No, no.

55
00:04:26,520 --> 00:04:27,640
It's about that thing from last time.

56
00:04:28,120 --> 00:04:28,640
My son

57
00:04:28,640 --> 00:04:30,040
just called.

58
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:31,080
He wants to renovate early.

59
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:32,520
He'll be too busy later.

60
00:04:32,840 --> 00:04:33,200
So,

61
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:34,400
I have to come over again.

62
00:04:34,640 --> 00:04:35,960
Right, right,

63
00:04:36,159 --> 00:04:37,400
I've kept it in mind.

64
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:39,880
It's just we really have too much

65
00:04:39,880 --> 00:04:40,400
going on at home

66
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:41,360
lately.

67
00:04:42,280 --> 00:04:42,720
How about

68
00:04:43,520 --> 00:04:45,920
you give me two more days?

69
00:04:47,320 --> 00:04:48,240
You know

70
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:49,200
what my son's like.

71
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:50,520
You can't argue with him.

72
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:53,040
It's all for the kids, right?

73
00:04:53,320 --> 00:04:54,159
Let's understand each other.

74
00:04:55,320 --> 00:04:56,240
Just hurry it up.

75
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:57,040
I'll get going.

76
00:04:57,480 --> 00:04:58,240
Take care of yourself.

77
00:04:58,240 --> 00:04:58,600
Okay.

78
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:14,000
Who isn't doing it for the kids, huh?

79
00:05:43,720 --> 00:05:43,960
Come on.

80
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:44,840
Get in.

81
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:46,440
Sir, the number's 2156.

82
00:05:46,760 --> 00:05:47,000
Got it.

83
00:05:52,040 --> 00:05:54,080
There are tissues on the back seat.

84
00:05:54,080 --> 00:05:54,640
Thanks.

85
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:00,040
Son, you okay?

86
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:01,520
I'm fine.

87
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:06,080
Sometimes

88
00:06:06,480 --> 00:06:07,440
you don't feel it right away.

89
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:08,880
Whenever you do,

90
00:06:08,880 --> 00:06:10,120
you tell me.

91
00:06:13,520 --> 00:06:14,520
Please fasten your seat belt.

92
00:06:14,520 --> 00:06:15,480
We're heading out.

93
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:16,240
Okay.

94
00:06:24,400 --> 00:06:25,120
It protected nothing.

95
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:29,520
Sir,

96
00:06:30,440 --> 00:06:31,400
could you go a bit faster?

97
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:32,920
My delivery's about to time out.

98
00:06:33,320 --> 00:06:34,960
You should swing by a hospital first.

99
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:35,800
No, I'm fine.

100
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:37,680
Just drop me at the intersection

101
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:38,360
up ahead on Jianshe Road.

102
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:43,440
What happened?

103
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:45,280
I fell.

104
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:47,760
Bike's wrecked too.

105
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:49,760
I called the client to explain,

106
00:06:49,760 --> 00:06:50,960
but he just wouldn't hear it.

107
00:06:54,640 --> 00:06:55,600
Said I'm scamming him,

108
00:06:56,320 --> 00:06:58,360
said if I'm late he'll complain.

109
00:06:58,920 --> 00:07:00,080
If I get a complaint,

110
00:07:00,080 --> 00:07:01,040
they'll dock my pay.

111
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:02,160
You see,

112
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:03,680
honestly,

113
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:04,600
in rain this heavy,

114
00:07:04,880 --> 00:07:06,400
you can't get a cab anywhere.

115
00:07:06,880 --> 00:07:08,080
If I wasn't desperate to deliver,

116
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:10,080
I'd never splurge on a ride.

117
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:12,080
I'm raising this kid alone,

118
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:14,160
I can't leave him home alone,

119
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:15,920
so I bring him along on runs.

120
00:07:16,760 --> 00:07:17,560
I just don't get it.

121
00:07:18,880 --> 00:07:20,080
Why is life this hard?

122
00:07:23,640 --> 00:07:24,160
I really feel like

123
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:25,640
I'm already doing my best.

124
00:08:09,440 --> 00:08:10,120
Ailing,

125
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:12,160
I'm dropping some things off.

126
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:13,320
If you're not home

127
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:14,360
I'll leave them at your door,

128
00:08:14,520 --> 00:08:15,560
so you can take them in later.

129
00:08:22,120 --> 00:08:23,200
Hurry up.

130
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:25,320
Give me a small one.

131
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:26,600
There's only room for one more.

132
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:29,600
Ailing.

133
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:30,880
Sister.

134
00:08:31,080 --> 00:08:32,240
Where are you going?

135
00:08:33,559 --> 00:08:34,360
Why are you here?

136
00:08:34,919 --> 00:08:36,440
To bring you some things.

137
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:38,960
Where are you off to?

138
00:08:39,919 --> 00:08:40,520
We're...

139
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:42,159
- Going out.
- Moving.

140
00:08:56,680 --> 00:08:58,760
You sold your home ten years ago?

141
00:09:00,240 --> 00:09:01,880
If I hadn't run into you today,

142
00:09:02,240 --> 00:09:03,240
were you planning to keep this

143
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:04,200
from me for another 10 or 20 years,

144
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:05,560
or your whole life?

145
00:09:08,360 --> 00:09:09,480
You clearly don't see me

146
00:09:09,480 --> 00:09:10,080
as your sister.

147
00:09:12,560 --> 00:09:13,960
Back when you were at teachers' college,

148
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:17,480
you came to me about everything.

149
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:22,400
Exams, graduation,

150
00:09:22,400 --> 00:09:23,360
boyfriends.

151
00:09:24,280 --> 00:09:25,280
Back then

152
00:09:25,280 --> 00:09:26,280
you weren't financially independent,

153
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:28,640
felt you lived off me, right?

154
00:09:30,160 --> 00:09:31,600
You can fly on your own now

155
00:09:31,760 --> 00:09:32,760
and I'm retired,

156
00:09:32,760 --> 00:09:33,760
so I can't help much anymore.

157
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:36,080
Selling the flat's a big thing,

158
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:37,600
and you wouldn't even consult me?

159
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:38,560
You don't even have a place

160
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:39,240
that's truly your own.

161
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:40,480
How did your life end up

162
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:41,480
like this?

163
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:48,240
I'm sorry.

164
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:00,040
I shouldn't scold you now.

165
00:10:01,320 --> 00:10:02,520
Don't cry.

166
00:10:08,720 --> 00:10:09,400
Please.

167
00:10:11,640 --> 00:10:13,320
If Mom could see you like this,

168
00:10:13,440 --> 00:10:14,600
she'd blame me.

169
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:17,280
I'm sorry.

170
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:19,120
I haven't been paying attention to you.

171
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:31,800
Where've you been?

172
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:44,280
I tried to find you this morning

173
00:10:44,520 --> 00:10:45,200
but you were swamped.

174
00:10:45,920 --> 00:10:46,640
Went looking for you this afternoon

175
00:10:46,640 --> 00:10:47,480
and you were gone again.

176
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:49,280
Let me ask you,

177
00:10:49,280 --> 00:10:50,480
why did you tell Zhang Ran

178
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:51,560
about me and Fu Yongjun?

179
00:10:52,120 --> 00:10:53,600
Now everyone's awkward.

180
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:55,280
From now on,

181
00:10:55,280 --> 00:10:55,880
don't

182
00:10:56,440 --> 00:10:57,440
tell her family stuff, okay?

183
00:11:12,080 --> 00:11:14,240
I saw you at the Chinese supermarket

184
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:14,920
last week.

185
00:11:15,160 --> 00:11:16,160
You had two kids with you.

186
00:11:17,280 --> 00:11:18,240
Then why didn't you call out to me?

187
00:11:18,760 --> 00:11:20,040
I didn't want to bother you.

188
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:22,240
Nonsense.

189
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:25,120
I noticed your daughter

190
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:26,320
looks just like you.

191
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:27,640
Yeah.

192
00:11:28,120 --> 00:11:29,040
You've never heard that?

193
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:30,160
Daughters take after their dads,

194
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:31,160
sons take after their moms.

195
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:34,320
But my girl's temper

196
00:11:34,320 --> 00:11:35,320
is more like her mother.

197
00:11:36,480 --> 00:11:37,560
She doesn't talk much,

198
00:11:37,560 --> 00:11:38,840
a bit icy.

199
00:11:39,160 --> 00:11:40,760
You're not much of a talker either.

200
00:11:42,040 --> 00:11:43,200
Oh, come on.

201
00:11:43,520 --> 00:11:45,800
I think I can chatter

202
00:11:46,160 --> 00:11:47,160
- non-stop.
- Since when?

203
00:11:49,440 --> 00:11:50,960
Depends who I'm with, I guess.

204
00:11:51,440 --> 00:11:52,160
Sometimes

205
00:11:52,160 --> 00:11:52,920
you see certain people

206
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:54,840
and you just can't think of

207
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:55,760
a single word to say.

208
00:11:58,840 --> 00:12:00,280
Back when my wife and I

209
00:12:00,280 --> 00:12:01,320
were home,

210
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:02,280
we'd each

211
00:12:02,640 --> 00:12:03,920
curl up with a book,

212
00:12:04,680 --> 00:12:05,480
sit in

213
00:12:06,720 --> 00:12:08,440
our own corners

214
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:09,880
all afternoon

215
00:12:10,840 --> 00:12:12,280
without saying a word.

216
00:12:12,680 --> 00:12:13,240
But just knowing

217
00:12:13,240 --> 00:12:14,800
someone else is in the room with you,

218
00:12:15,840 --> 00:12:17,040
that feels pretty good.

219
00:12:19,880 --> 00:12:21,440
A cup of coffee, a book,

220
00:12:21,920 --> 00:12:23,000
and a whole day like that,

221
00:12:23,520 --> 00:12:24,080
sounds perfect.

222
00:12:27,840 --> 00:12:28,800
But when she

223
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:30,480
asked for a divorce,

224
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:31,040
she said

225
00:12:34,160 --> 00:12:35,120
she wanted a life

226
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:37,320
with real everyday warmth.

227
00:12:37,320 --> 00:12:40,040
A life where you can actually argue.

228
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:46,400
She likes arguing?

229
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:49,720
It's not what you think.

230
00:12:49,720 --> 00:12:51,040
Sometimes arguing

231
00:12:51,040 --> 00:12:52,480
is just another way of talking.

232
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:56,080
What I mean is that

233
00:12:57,960 --> 00:13:00,080
if two people can still fight,

234
00:13:00,240 --> 00:13:02,000
nothing truly huge has broken yet.

235
00:13:02,720 --> 00:13:05,000
When you can't even fight anymore,

236
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:06,920
that's when things are really bad.

237
00:13:22,720 --> 00:13:24,320
You're that hot-and-sour noodles girl,

238
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:24,640
right?

239
00:13:28,840 --> 00:13:29,520
I ordered in your live stream.

240
00:13:31,280 --> 00:13:31,920
Thanks.

241
00:13:32,760 --> 00:13:34,480
Online you're so loud and bouncy.

242
00:13:35,040 --> 00:13:37,080
In real life you're pretty quiet.

243
00:13:39,320 --> 00:13:40,760
Because you don't know me yet.

244
00:13:58,280 --> 00:13:59,000
It's so late

245
00:13:59,000 --> 00:13:59,920
and you're still on the road?

246
00:14:01,760 --> 00:14:03,400
Once I drop you off, I'm done.

247
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:05,440
Wife and kid are waiting at home.

248
00:16:17,080 --> 00:16:17,800
Coming.

249
00:16:28,400 --> 00:16:29,080
Coming.

250
00:16:30,240 --> 00:16:31,640
No, no, don't jump.

251
00:16:37,160 --> 00:16:37,920
Here's your express delivery.

252
00:16:37,920 --> 00:16:38,520
Thanks.

253
00:16:38,760 --> 00:16:39,600
Weather's bad today.

254
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:40,840
Sorry I'm late.

255
00:16:42,160 --> 00:16:42,840
What happened to your face?

256
00:16:43,120 --> 00:16:43,840
Took a spill.

257
00:16:46,080 --> 00:16:46,560
Stop.

258
00:16:47,480 --> 00:16:48,200
Sorry,

259
00:16:48,200 --> 00:16:48,920
making you run deliveries

260
00:16:48,920 --> 00:16:50,160
in this kind of rain.

261
00:16:50,160 --> 00:16:50,680
It's my job.

262
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:51,400
Well,

263
00:16:51,680 --> 00:16:52,680
it's tough running parcels.

264
00:16:52,680 --> 00:16:54,120
Could you give us a good review?

265
00:16:54,120 --> 00:16:54,800
Sure.

266
00:16:54,800 --> 00:16:55,600
Great, thanks.

267
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:56,800
Thanks.

268
00:16:58,080 --> 00:16:59,200
Okay, we'll get going.

269
00:16:59,640 --> 00:17:00,120
Wait.

270
00:17:01,280 --> 00:17:01,560
Hang on.

271
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:04,920
No, that's not necessary.

272
00:17:04,920 --> 00:17:05,359
Thank you so much.

273
00:17:05,359 --> 00:17:06,200
You don't have to.

274
00:17:07,160 --> 00:17:07,800
Thank you.

275
00:17:07,800 --> 00:17:09,520
Here, kiddo, have some water.

276
00:17:09,520 --> 00:17:10,560
I'll open it for you.

277
00:17:11,440 --> 00:17:12,280
What should you say?

278
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:14,040
Thank you.

279
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:15,119
You're welcome.

280
00:17:15,680 --> 00:17:16,440
Come on, let's go.

281
00:17:17,560 --> 00:17:18,119
Sir,

282
00:17:19,040 --> 00:17:20,359
you look even better in person.

283
00:17:21,760 --> 00:17:23,160
Okay, we're off.

284
00:17:26,960 --> 00:17:27,640
I'll press it for you.

285
00:17:27,640 --> 00:17:28,200
No need.

286
00:17:28,760 --> 00:17:29,920
This might go a bit faster.

287
00:17:32,160 --> 00:17:32,920
Tough job you've got.

288
00:17:33,280 --> 00:17:33,880
Yeah.

289
00:17:35,160 --> 00:17:35,920
Your leg

290
00:17:36,520 --> 00:17:37,480
seems badly hurt...

291
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:38,040
It's fine.

292
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:39,240
It's nothing.

293
00:17:40,720 --> 00:17:41,280
We'll head out.

294
00:17:41,680 --> 00:17:42,720
You should see the doctor.

295
00:17:42,720 --> 00:17:43,360
Okay.

296
00:19:20,520 --> 00:19:21,360
Zhang Jianbin?

297
00:19:25,600 --> 00:19:26,200
Zhang Jianbin?

298
00:19:27,120 --> 00:19:28,120
